iately. ``` client.connectionPool().evictAll(); ``` If your client has a cache, call [close()][Cache.close]. Note that it is an error to create calls against a cache that is closed, and doing so will cause the call to crash. ``` client.cache().close(); ``` OkHttp also uses daemon threads for HTTP/2 connections. These will exit automatically if they remain idle.
